The heartbroken 34-year-old has revealed that her face had been so botched from surgery that she couldn't smile at her newborn when she gave birth in 2011.

Alicia, who has undergone over 350 procedures and spent £1.2million on surgery since the age of 17, has two daughters, Georgia, 17, and 16-month-old Papaya.

She told The Sun: ' Imagine holding 
your baby daughter for the for the first time and not being able to 
smile. I have been so selfish. Now my dream is for Papaya one day to see her mummy smile back at her for the first time.'

Alicia also admitted her guilt at 
forcing older daughter Georgia to miss an important GCSE exam so that she 
could babysit while Alicia underwent yet another procedure.

