As
well as losing her once lovely looks and not being able to move her 
face naturally, Alicia is unable to drink normally, and is often in pain.

She
first went under the knife when she was 17, and since then has had six 
nose jobs, 11 procedures on the skin around her eyes, cheek implants 
(both adding and removal) and a facelift.

Alicia says she also had a rib shortened to give her a slimmer silhouette, her toes
shortened ‘so they looked better in heels’, a tummy tuck, bottom 
implants, chin implants and 16 breast augmentations.

Alicia believes that she has an 
addiction to surgery and blames the surgeons who allowed her to 
disfigure herself when she was such a pretty young women.

